pageContext.description: Flat wings, edges slightly bevelled. Midrib very prominent: shoulders rectangular; loops ear-like, their sides ridged and produced on to the blade as a low rib for a short distance; rivet holes absent.
pageContext.patina: Green patina flaked with very dark brown: metal showing through chiefly on one face.
pageContext.surface: Corroded and eaten into and flaky. At the joint of the wings and socket there are several long holes.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Cambridge,Foster Bequest (Cat. 290),Prehistoric Bronzes (Cat. 173). Catalogue Lost,z.4300
